# Report Variables

The report variables are found under **Variables** → **Report-Variables.tex** in the LaTeX sidebar. This file centralizes all the inputs that populate the cover page, and executive summary. Fill everything out here and it propagates automatically throughout the report.

The variables are organized into three blocks.

---

## Report and Students

These variables populate part of the **cover page** and part of the **Facility Overview** of the report.

```latex
\newcommand{\ReportNumber}{--}
\newcommand{\VisitDate}{--}
\newcommand{\StudentLead}{--}
\newcommand{\SafetyLead}{--}
\providecommand{\StudentList}{Student 1, Student 2, Student 3}
\newcommand{\StudentRows}{%
    Student 1 \\
    & Student 2 \\
    & Student 3 %
}
```

| Variable | What to enter |
|---|---|
| `\ReportNumber` | The report number assigned to this assessment |
| `\VisitDate` | Date of the on-site assessment |
| `\StudentLead` | The student assigned as lead for this assessment — typically the person filling out the report |
| `\SafetyLead` | The student assigned as safety lead |
| `\StudentList` | Comma-separated list of **all** students who attended, including the student lead and safety lead (used in the Facility Overview closing sentence) |
| `\StudentRows` | All attending students **except** the student lead and safety lead, each on its own line (used in the cover page student table) |

 "StudentList vs. StudentRows"
    These two variables look similar but are used in different places and contain different people:

   **`\StudentList`** — everyone who attended, including student lead and safety lead. Used in the Facility Overview paragraph.
   
   **`\StudentRows`** — everyone *except* the student lead and safety lead. Used in the cover page table, where the lead and safety lead already appear in their own labeled rows.

Omitting the student lead or safety lead from `\StudentList`, or accidentally including them in `\StudentRows`, will cause incorrect names to appear on the cover page.


