## Overall Recommendation Variables


These variables are filled in **after the report is complete**, once all recommendations have been written and their savings calculated. They feed into the **executive summary** and the totals row of the **Summary of Recommendations** table.

```latex
\newcommand{\TotalRecImplementation}{--}
\newcommand{\TotalRecSavings}{--}
\newcommand{\TotalkWhSavings}{--}
\newcommand{\TotalkWSavings}{--}
\newcommand{\TotalGasSavings}{--}
```

| Variable | What to enter |
|---|---|
| `\TotalRecImplementation` | Total estimated implementation cost across all recommendations ($) |
| `\TotalRecSavings` | Total estimated annual cost savings across all recommendations ($/yr) |
| `\TotalkWhSavings` | Total annual electricity savings across all recommendations (kWh/yr) |
| `\TotalkWSavings` | Total peak demand savings across all recommendations (kW-months) |
| `\TotalGasSavings` | Total annual natural gas savings across all recommendations (therms/yr or MMBtu/yr, consistent with the report) |

**Fill these in last!**
    Do not estimate or partially fill in these totals during the writing process. Complete all individual recommendations first, then sum the values and enter them here. Entering preliminary numbers risks leaving incorrect totals in the final report.
